FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1780920676
OL,3,CMan pleads guilty to murder of Sarah
OL,4,CMontgomery
OL,6,FAs Ms Montgomery's loved ones sat in
OL,7,Fthe public gallery of Belfast Crown
OL,8,FCourt, Hughes appeared in the dock
OL,9,Fflanked by two prison officers.
OL,11,FHis solicitor David Jones addressed
OL,12,FMadam Justice McBride and said that
OL,13,Fwhilst this was a case affected by the
OL,14,Fcurrent withdrawal of services, the
OL,15,Farraignment could go ahead.
OL,17,FMr Jones added: "The accused is aware
OL,18,Fof the consequences of the action he
OL,19,Fis about to take and the arraignment
OL,20,Fcan proceed, My Lady."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1780920676
OL,3,CMan pleads guilty to murder of Sarah
OL,4,CMontgomery
OL,6,FFrom Ardglen Place in Belfast, Hughes
OL,7,Fwas asked to stand by a court clerk
OL,8,Fwho then charged him with the murder
OL,9,Fof Ms Montgomery.
OL,11,FWhen asked how he pleaded to the
OL,12,Fcharge, Hughes replied "guilty."
OL,14,FHughes was then charged with 'intent
OL,15,Fto destroy the life of a child capable
OL,16,Fof being born alive by a willful act,
OL,17,Fcaused a child to die before it had an
OL,18,Fexistence independent of its mother'
OL,19,Fon the same date.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1780920676
OL,3,CMan pleads guilty to murder of Sarah
OL,4,CMontgomery
OL,6,FTo his second charge, Hughes again
OL,7,Freplied "guilty."
OL,9,FFollowing this, Hughes was addressed
OL,10,Fby Madam Justice McBride who told him:
OL,11,F"In light of the pleas there is only
OL,12,Fone sentence of imprisonment that I
OL,13,Fcan impose and that is one of life
OL,14,Fimprisonment.
OL,16,F"Before I can set a tariff, you may
OL,17,Fwish to have some further evidence and
OL,18,Freports."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
